{%- comment -%}
  Builds alt text for a product image, generating a fallback when the image has
  none of its own.

  Inventory syncs in from marketplaces with empty alt text, so a one-time
  backfill in the admin would go stale with every new listing. Generating at
  render time keeps every image covered, including products that don't exist yet.

  Accepts:
  - alt_source:    {String} Existing alt text, used as-is when present
  - product_title: {String} Product title, used to build the fallback
  - position:      {Number} (optional) This image's index
  - total:         {Number} (optional) Total image count
  - suffix:        {String} (optional) Used instead of "photo X of Y"

  Outputs UNESCAPED text. Escape at the call site for raw alt="" attributes;
  pass it straight to image_tag, which escapes its own attribute values.

  Usage:
  {%- capture image_alt %}{% render 'aeonic-image-alt',
    alt_source: media.alt, product_title: product.title,
    position: position, total: media_count %}{% endcapture -%}
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- liquid
  assign aeonic_alt = alt_source | default: '' | strip

  if aeonic_alt == blank
    assign aeonic_alt = product_title | default: '' | strip | truncate: 100

    if aeonic_alt != blank
      if suffix != blank
        assign aeonic_alt = aeonic_alt | append: ' — ' | append: suffix
      elsif position != blank and total != blank and total > 1
        assign aeonic_alt = aeonic_alt | append: ' — photo ' | append: position | append: ' of ' | append: total
      endif
    endif
  endif
-%}
{{- aeonic_alt -}}
